SIMPLE: imbroglio
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imbroglio
<hw>Im*brogl"io</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Imbroglios</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>embroglio</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[It. See 1st <er>Broil</er>, and cf.
<er>Embroil</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An intricate, complicated
plot, as of a drama or work of fiction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A complicated and embarrassing state of things; a
serious misunderstanding or disagreement, especially one that is
bitter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wrestling to free itself from the baleful
<qex>imbroglio</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbrown</ent>⟦br⟧
